	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>his is going to be a simple guide to get a bard started in his young life. The absolute FIRST thing you do is find your bards guild<br>                        and turn in you letter to Sylia. she will give u a tunic and you are now registered with your guild. Don't worry about the spiderling<br>                        silk quest she gives out, because your need a couple lvls to do it. <br><br>                        Travel down the newbie lift (there are 3 lifts: newbie, Priest of Discord, and orc. familiarize yourself with these as they are great<br>                        landmarks when running around or meeting someone) and head out to the right. this is the newbie area, where you need to kill<br>                        bats during your first two lvls. You can take wasps at 2nd lvl, but don't mess with spiderlings or orc pawns till atleast 3rd. i<br>                        personally wouldn't kill any wolves because they lower your faction with certain druid npc's. <br><br>                        Once you hit 3rd or 4th lvl, go back to your guild and hail Sylia. she'll tell you about a guild quest of collecting 4 spiderling silks for<br>                        lute strings. these come off of the spiderlings in the newbie zone, so hop down there and slash away. this quest gives good xp,<br>                        some gold, and a hand drum, which you can keep or sell. <br><br>                        Once you hit 5th lvl its time to hit orc hill. Go there with a group because there can be some tough pulls there sometimes. This is<br>                        good xp if you don't die too much. I would stay here till lvl 7, then fight in the tunnel in cb until 8. once you hit 8 you can group<br>                        and kill slavers in the slave caves in Crushbone. You can stay in cb till lvl 17, but that is up to you. <br><br>                        One thing i neglected to mention earlier were skills. You should put one practice into bind wounds, and one point into each<br>                        instrument skill as it becomes available. These skills go up so quickly on their own that you need not train in them. <br><br>                        On a last note, the cb centurion belts and leggonaire pads should be kept and stored. These are turned in to Canloe Nusback in<br>                        the warriors guild in Kaladim for GREAT xp and patchwork armour and gold. Once you get a steady stream of these belts and<br>                        pads you can get a lvl a day till 12 or 13. <br><br>                        thank you for listening to my humble suggestions, i hope they are of assistance. i'll be posting a thread on song twisting soon.<br>                        Be safe and good hunting, <br><br>                        Argalen, 10lvl bard on Bertoxx <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
