<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100099723645874></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100099723645874><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100099723645874>Reply: Why dex?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100099723645874#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=51518><span id= >Tusin</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 20th 10:47 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>   As a "psuedo casting class" you have the curse of all caster, your songs can be interupted by being hit. Thus you should allocate more points into dex than any other stat (other than cha). This will allow you to play songs more consistantly without being interupted. Also, the more dex, the less times you see (Dinian missed a note)... that is really annoying!!!<br>   Charisma is what i consider the main bard stat, for alot of your soloing capabilites come from charming a monster ( lvl 27 song, pixie strike) and using it as a pet. Also, cha helps with casting fear (lvl 26 song) and allows you to mezz more mobs when you have multiple pulls and have to play the AOE mezz song. (not sure which lvl, but i think its 16 or so).<br>    I hope this info helps out all you people starting bards, and those who already have them. And remember, just because you didnt choose the right stats to start out with you can always keep that character, just get items that buff the stats you left out. After all, a Bard with high str would tank better than a bard with low str.<br>    Have fun yall, and keep the music alive.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
